               <head>Questions and <normalised orig="Answeres" auto="true">Answers</normalised>
<normalised orig="vpon" auto="true">upon</normalised> the Creed, the Ten <normalised orig="Commandements" auto="true">Commandments</normalised>,
the Sacraments, and
the Lords prayer; for the farther
opening of the <normalised orig="ordinarie" auto="true">ordinary</normalised>
<normalised orig="Catechisme" auto="true">Catechism</normalised>.</head>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Question.<lb/>
BY what <normalised orig="meanes" auto="true">means</normalised> art thou <normalised orig="receiued" auto="true">received</normalised><lb/>
into the Church of<lb/>
God?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. Outwardly by <normalised orig="baptisme" auto="true">baptism</normalised><lb/>
Act.2.41. but inwardly<lb/>
by faith in Christ, <normalised orig="Ro" auto="true">To</normalised>: 5.2.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. What benefits <normalised orig="receiued" auto="true">received</normalised> you by<lb/>
<normalised orig="baptisme" auto="true">baptism</normalised>?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. Three: first I was made a member<lb/>
of Christ, 1. Cor. 6.15.<lb/>
Secondly, I was adopted the <normalised orig="childe" auto="true">child</normalised> of<lb/>
God, <notvariant>Rom</notvariant>: 9.26 Gal: 4.5.<lb/>
Thirdly, I was made the <normalised orig="heire" auto="true">heir</normalised> of the<lb/>
kingdom of <normalised orig="glorie" auto="true">glory</normalised>, <notvariant>Rom</notvariant>: 8.17.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. Seeing by <normalised orig="Baptisme" auto="true">Baptism</normalised> thou art <normalised orig="receiued" auto="true">received</normalised><lb/>
into the Church of Christ, what<lb/>
                     <pb n="1"/>
                     <lb/>
<normalised orig="vse" auto="true">use</normalised> is there of Godfathers and Godmothers<lb/>
therein?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. First, they did present me to the<lb/>
Church instead of my Parents, <normalised orig="Luk" auto="true">Luck</normalised>. 2.22.<lb/>
Secondly, they made confession of that<lb/>
faith, into the which I was to be Baptised.<lb/>
Thirdly, they promised and vowed on<lb/>
my <normalised orig="behalfe" auto="true">behalf</normalised>, what on my part was to <normalised orig="bee" auto="true">be</normalised><lb/>
performed.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. What did they promise on your<lb/>
<normalised orig="behalfe" auto="true">behalf</normalised>?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. They promised three things, First,<lb/>
that I should forsake the three <normalised orig="capitall" auto="true">capital</normalised> enemies<lb/>
of my <normalised orig="saluation" auto="true">salvation</normalised>, the World, the<lb/>
Flesh, and the <normalised orig="Diuell" auto="true">Devil</normalised>, 1. <notvariant>Ioh</notvariant>. 2 14 15<lb/>
Secondly, that I should <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised> all the<lb/>
Articles of the Christian faith, Act. 16.31<lb/>
Thirdly, that I should <normalised orig="keepe" auto="true">keep</normalised> all Gods<lb/>
<normalised orig="Commandements" auto="true">Commandments</normalised> all the <normalised orig="dayes" auto="true">days</normalised> of my life,<lb/>
<notvariant>Deut</notvariant>. 6.2.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. <notvariant>Dost</notvariant> thou <normalised orig="thinke" auto="true">think</normalised>, that thou art<lb/>
bound to <normalised orig="performe" auto="true">perform</normalised> these things promised?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. Yea verily, in regard of the <normalised orig="couenant" auto="true">covenant</normalised><lb/>
which I <normalised orig="haue" auto="true">have</normalised> made with GOD,<lb/>
Hos. 2.23.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. Art thou able to <normalised orig="performe" auto="true">perform</normalised> all<lb/>
                     <pb n="2"/>
                     <lb/>
these things?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. Not of my <normalised orig="selfe" auto="true">self</normalised>, but in some measure<lb/>
I am enabled thereunto by Gods<lb/>
grace, Phil. 4.13.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. What is <normalised orig="vnderstood" auto="true">understood</normalised> by the first<lb/>
<normalised orig="capitall" auto="true">capital</normalised> <normalised orig="enemie" auto="true">enemy</normalised>, the World?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. I <normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised> <normalised orig="vnderstand" auto="true">understand</normalised> all outward<lb/>
and earthly things: as <normalised orig="euill" auto="true">evil</normalised> company, riches,<lb/>
honour, pleasure, and such like: as<lb/>
they are <normalised orig="meanes" auto="true">means</normalised> to draw <normalised orig="mee" auto="true">me</normalised> from God,<lb/>
1. <notvariant>Ioh</notvariant>. 2.15. 1. <notvariant>Ioh</notvariant>. 5.19.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. What is meant by the Flesh?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. By the Flesh I <normalised orig="meane" auto="true">mean</normalised> our corrupt<lb/>
nature, inclined to <normalised orig="euill" auto="true">evil</normalised>, <normalised orig="vncleane" auto="true">unclean</normalised> lusts,<lb/>
<normalised orig="euill" auto="true">evil</normalised> desires, whereby our will is often <normalised orig="depraued" auto="true">depraved</normalised><lb/>
&amp; <normalised orig="peruerted" auto="true">perverted</normalised>, <notvariant>Rom</notvariant>. 7.18. Gal. 5.17.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="meane" auto="true">mean</normalised> you by the <normalised orig="Diuell" auto="true">Devil</normalised>?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. I <normalised orig="meane" auto="true">mean</normalised> all those spirits of <normalised orig="Apostacie" auto="true">Apostasy</normalised>,<lb/>
<normalised orig="euer" auto="true">ever</normalised> at hand to suggest <normalised orig="euill" auto="true">evil</normalised> motions<lb/>
into mine heart, <notvariant>Ioh</notvariant>. 13.2.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. You <normalised orig="sayd" auto="true">said</normalised> that you are also bound<lb/>
to <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised>. What is faith?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. Faith is a grace <normalised orig="giuen" auto="true">given</normalised> of God to<lb/>
assure me of his mercy and <normalised orig="loue" auto="true">love</normalised> <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> me in<lb/>
Christ. <notvariant>Rom</notvariant> 8.38 <normalised orig="reuealed" auto="true">revealed</normalised> <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> my <normalised orig="minde" auto="true">mind</normalised><lb/>
by the holy Ghost, Gal. 4.6. through the <normalised orig="ministery" auto="true">ministry</normalised><lb/>
of the word, <notvariant>Ioh</notvariant>. 17.20. <normalised orig="Ro" auto="true">To</normalised>. 10.17.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <pb n="3"/>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. What are these things which we<lb/>
are to <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised> <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> <normalised orig="saluation" auto="true">salvation</normalised>?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. We must <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised> all those <normalised orig="fundamentall" auto="true">fundamental</normalised><lb/>
points laid <normalised orig="downe" auto="true">down</normalised> <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised> in the<lb/>
word, <notvariant>Ioh</notvariant>. 20.31. the <normalised orig="summe" auto="true">sum</normalised> whereof is<lb/>
expressed in the Creed, commonly called<lb/>
the Apostles Creed.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. Rehearse the Creed.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. I <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised> in God the Father, <normalised orig="almightie" auto="true">almighty</normalised>.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. Into how many <normalised orig="partes" auto="true">parts</normalised> is this<lb/>
Creed <normalised orig="diuided" auto="true">divided</normalised>?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. Into <normalised orig="foure" auto="true">four</normalised> <normalised orig="partes" auto="true">parts</normalised> <normalised orig="contayning" auto="true">containing</normalised><lb/>
<normalised orig="twelue" auto="true">twelve</normalised> Articles: in the first whereof I am<lb/>
taught to <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised> in God the Father, who<lb/>
<normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> made me and all creatures, in the first<lb/>
Article: in the second part I am taught to<lb/>
<normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised> in God the <normalised orig="Sonne" auto="true">Son</normalised>, who <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> redeemed<lb/>
me and all <normalised orig="mankinde" auto="true">mankind</normalised>, in the six next<lb/>
Articles.<lb/>
In the third part I am taught to <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised><lb/>
in God the Holy Ghost, who <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> sanctified<lb/>
me &amp; all the elect, in the eight Article.<lb/>
In the fourth part I am taught to <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised><lb/>
concerning the Church as is laid<lb/>
<normalised orig="downe" auto="true">down</normalised> in the <normalised orig="foure" auto="true">four</normalised> last articles.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="doest" auto="false">do</normalised> thou <normalised orig="learne" auto="true">learn</normalised> to <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised><lb/>
                     <pb n="4"/>
                     <lb/>
in the first article, I <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised> in God the<lb/>
Father <normalised orig="Almightie" auto="true">Almighty</normalised> maker of <normalised orig="heauen" auto="true">heaven</normalised> and earth?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. I <normalised orig="learne" auto="true">learn</normalised> to <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised> <normalised orig="foure" auto="true">four</normalised> things:<lb/>
First that there is a God, <notvariant>Isai</notvariant>. 45.21.22.<lb/>
Secondly, that this God is but one,<lb/>
1. Cor. 8.6. 1 Tim. 2.5.<lb/>
Thirdly, that this one God is distinguished,<lb/>
into three <normalised orig="persones" auto="true">persons</normalised>, Father, Son,<lb/>
and holy Ghost, 1. <notvariant>Ioh</notvariant>. 5.7.<lb/>
Fourthly, that this one God is almighty,<lb/>
<normalised orig="declard" auto="false">declared</normalised> so to be first by creating all<lb/>
things, Gen. 1.1.<lb/>
Secondly, by <normalised orig="vpholding" auto="true">upholding</normalised> all things created<lb/>
by his <normalised orig="continuall" auto="true">continual</normalised> <normalised orig="prouidence" auto="true">providence</normalised>, Psalm:<lb/>
145.15.16. Act: 17.28.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. This thou <normalised orig="beleeuest" auto="true">believe</normalised>, but what<lb/>
comfort <notvariant>reapest</notvariant> thou thereby <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> thy<lb/>
<normalised orig="selfe" auto="true">self</normalised>?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. First I do <normalised orig="beleeue" auto="true">believe</normalised> that God is my<lb/>
Father, and that I am his child, <notvariant>Ioh</notvariant> 1.12.<lb/>
Gal: 3.26.<lb/>
Secondly, that he being <normalised orig="almightie" auto="true">almighty</normalised> and<lb/>
I his <normalised orig="childe" auto="true">child</normalised>, <normalised orig="hee" auto="true">he</normalised> will <normalised orig="giue" auto="true">give</normalised> <normalised orig="mee" auto="true">me</normalised> all things<lb/>
<normalised orig="needfull" auto="true">needful</normalised>, Psalm: 34.10. and <normalised orig="preserue" auto="true">preserve</normalised> <normalised orig="mee" auto="true">me</normalised><lb/>
from all dangers <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> <normalised orig="saluation" auto="true">salvation</normalised>, 2. Tim:<lb/>
4.18.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. Touching the second Article,<lb/>
                     <pb n="5"/>
                     <lb/>
why is the <normalised orig="Sonne" auto="true">Son</normalised> of God called <normalised orig="Iesus" auto="true">Jesus</normalised>?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. Because <normalised orig="hee" auto="true">he</normalised> <normalised orig="saueth" auto="true">saves</normalised> <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised> from all<lb/>
our <normalised orig="sinnes" auto="true">sins</normalised>, Math. 1.21. neither is there<lb/>
<normalised orig="saluation" auto="true">salvation</normalised> in any other, Act. 4.12.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. Wherefore is he called Christ?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. In regard of his Offices <normalised orig="wherevnto" auto="true">whereunto</normalised><lb/>
he was ordained by God the Father,<lb/>
<notvariant>Ioh</notvariant>. 6.27. and <normalised orig="anoynted" auto="true">anointed</normalised> by the holy Ghost,<lb/>
Math. 3.16.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. Which are the Offices of Christ?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. First, his Office <normalised orig="Propheticall" auto="true">Prophetical</normalised><lb/>
to instruct <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised> in all things, <notvariant>Deut</notvariant>. 18.15.<lb/>
<normalised orig="Esay" auto="true">Essay</normalised>. 61.1.<lb/>
Secondly, his Priestly Office to <normalised orig="redeeme" auto="true">redeem</normalised><lb/>
<normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised>, <notvariant>Hebr</notvariant>. 7.21. <notvariant>Heb</notvariant>. 9.11. and to<lb/>
pray for <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised>, <notvariant>Rom</notvariant> 8.34.<lb/>
Thirdly, his Kingly Office, to <normalised orig="raigne" auto="true">reign</normalised><lb/>
<normalised orig="ouer" auto="true">over</normalised> <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised> by his spirit and word, <normalised orig="Luk" auto="true">Luck</normalised>. 1.33.<lb/>
Act. 2.36.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. Why is he called the <normalised orig="onely" auto="true">only</normalised> begotten<lb/>
<normalised orig="sonne" auto="true">son</normalised> of God, since wee also are<lb/>
the <normalised orig="sonne" auto="true">son</normalised> of God?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. For that he <normalised orig="onely" auto="true">only</normalised> is the <normalised orig="Sonne" auto="true">Son</normalised> of<lb/>
God by nature and generation, <notvariant>Ioh</notvariant>. 1.14.<lb/>
but we are the <normalised orig="sonnes" auto="true">sons</normalised> of God by grace and<lb/>
                     <choice ana="illegible">
                        <sic><notvariant>adop</notvariant>*ion</sic>
                        <corr>adoption</corr>
                     </choice>, <notvariant>Rom</notvariant>. 8 15. Gal. 4.5.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised> you <normalised orig="learne" auto="true">learn</normalised> that <normalised orig="Iesus" auto="true">Jesus</normalised><lb/>
                     <pb n="6"/>
                     <lb/>
Christ is the <normalised orig="Sonne" auto="true">Son</normalised> of God by nature?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. I <normalised orig="learne" auto="true">learn</normalised> <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> my comfort, that he<lb/>
was very God, <notvariant>Ioh</notvariant>. 1.14. &amp; that <normalised orig="therfore" auto="true">therefore</normalised><lb/>
<normalised orig="whatsoeuer" auto="true">whatsoever</normalised> was performed and suffered<lb/>
by him was infinitely meritorious for<lb/>
our <normalised orig="saluation" auto="true">salvation</normalised>, Act. 20.28. 2. Cor. 5.19.<lb/>
Col. 1.19.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. Wherefore is <normalised orig="Iesus" auto="true">Jesus</normalised> Christ called<lb/>
our Lord?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. Because <normalised orig="hauing" auto="true">having</normalised> redeemed our<lb/>
<normalised orig="soules" auto="true">souls</normalised> from <normalised orig="sinne" auto="true">sin</normalised> and <normalised orig="Sathan" auto="true">Satan</normalised>, <normalised orig="hee" auto="true">he</normalised> <normalised orig="doth" auto="false">does</normalised><lb/>
challenge <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised>, as his <normalised orig="owne" auto="true">own</normalised> to <normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised> him <normalised orig="seruice" auto="true">service</normalised>,<lb/>
<notvariant>Rom</notvariant>. 14.8.9. 1. Cor. 6.19.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised> you <normalised orig="learne" auto="true">learn</normalised> out of the<lb/>
third Article, <normalised orig="Conceiued" auto="true">Conceived</normalised> by the holy Ghost,<lb/>
borne of the <normalised orig="Virgine" auto="true">Virgin</normalised> Mary?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. I <normalised orig="learne" auto="true">learn</normalised> first by his birth, that he<lb/>
was man that so <normalised orig="hee" auto="true">he</normalised> might suffer for my<lb/>
<normalised orig="sinne" auto="true">sin</normalised>, <notvariant>Heb</notvariant>. 2.14.15.<lb/>
Secondly, by the manner of his conception<lb/>
by the holy Ghost, and birth of a <normalised orig="virgine" auto="true">virgin</normalised>,<lb/>
that he was without all manner of<lb/>
<normalised orig="sinne" auto="true">sin</normalised> and so the sacrifice of <normalised orig="himselfe" auto="true">himself</normalised>, being<lb/>
most pure, it was precious for our <normalised orig="redemtion" auto="true">redemption</normalised>,<lb/>
1. Pet. 1.19.<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="a">
                  <p>Quest. What <normalised orig="learne" auto="true">learn</normalised> you out of the<lb/>
fourth Article, <normalised orig="Hee" auto="true">He</normalised> suffered <normalised orig="vnder" auto="true">under</normalised> Pontius<lb/>
                     <lb/>
                     <fw type="pageNum">B</fw>
                     <pb n="7"/>
                     <lb/>
Pilate, was crucified, dead and buried, <normalised orig="hee" auto="true">he</normalised> descended<lb/>
into Hell?<lb/>
                  </p>
               </sp>
               <sp who="b">
                  <p>Ans. I <normalised orig="learne" auto="true">learn</normalised>, that <normalised orig="vpon" auto="true">upon</normalised> the <normalised orig="Crosse" auto="true">Cross</normalised> he<lb/>
suffered both in his body and <normalised orig="soule" auto="true">soul</normalised>, <notvariant>Isai</notvariant>.<lb/>
